-- SEC’s Schapiro Said to Be Recovering After Surgery Last Week
-- B y   J o s h u a   G a l l u
-- 2012-09-17T20:01:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-17/sec-s-schapiro-said-to-be-recovering-after-surgery-last-week.html
U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission Chairman  Mary Schapiro  underwent surgery last week
and plans to return to the office on Sept. 19, according to a
person with knowledge of the matter.  Schapiro had the surgery on Thursday, Sept. 13, and has
been working from home since the following day, according to the
person, who asked not to be identified because the matter wasn’t
public. Florence Harmon, an SEC spokeswoman, declined to
comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joshua Gallu in Washington at 
